  "prompt": "Chamath Palihapitiya: How do you build/implant growth mindset in your team?",
  "response": "Here are key insights from Chamath Palihapitiya on building a growth mindset in teams:\n\n1. Create Psychological Safety\n- Encourage open dialogue\n- Make it safe to fail\n- Reward learning and experimentation\n- Don't punish honest mistakes\n\n2. Set Ambitious Goals\n- Challenge team beyond comfort zone\n- Create stretch objectives\n- Inspire people to think big\n- Focus on potential, not just current capabilities\n\n3. Embrace Continuous Learning\n- Promote constant skill development\n- Support ongoing education\n- Provide resources for personal growth\n- Treat learning as a core company value\n\n4. Lead by Example\n- Demonstrate vulnerability\n- Share your own learning experiences\n- Show how you adapt and improve\n- Model curiosity and openness\n\n5. Reward Progress, Not Just Outcomes\n- Acknowledge effort and improvement\n- Recognize learning processes\n- Celebrate strategic iterations\n- Value resilience and adaptability\n\n6. Foster Intrinsic Motivation\n- Help team understand deeper purpose\n- Connect individual roles to larger mission\n- Encourage autonomous decision-making\n- Build internal drive for excellence\n\n7. Create Feedback Culture\n- Implement regular, constructive feedback\n- Make feedback transparent and actionable\n- Encourage peer-to-peer coaching\n- View feedback as growth opportunity\n\nThese principles help create an environment where growth mindset naturally emerges.",
